cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM. 

The paper presents an approach to accelerating image processing operators using fully-convolutional networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the effect of network architecture on approximation accuracy, runtime, and memory footprint, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the approach on various image processing tasks, including nonphotorealistic stylization and photographic style transfer, which could place it in cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
